        <figure class=""stand_out"">

            <h3 class=""medium_heading""> II PEDAGOGICAL OBJECTIVES </h3>

            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 1. Origin of the program </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The course for the bachelor’s of Science in Education is generalist, in the view of a course of undergraduate level, in order to make it possible to
                    the students to include/understand the phenomena, the processes, the actors and institutions concerned in the field of education. The program
                    that we propose finds its origins with a view to filling the needs for Specialists in education, taking into consideration our sociocultural realities.
                    The students are thus brought to know gradually various approache");
            WriteLiteral(@"s in social sciences implemented to education, thought like initiations as well
                    as refering at the same time to the methods and fields mobilized by the disciplines of sociology, anthropology, philosophy, history, psychology,
                    psychoanalysis ; etc., as with the field specific to Education Sciences.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 2. Objectives of the program</h3>
                <h3 class=""smaller_heading""> II.2.1. General objective </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The disciplinary lessosn and initiated pedagogies are likely to better apprehend the phenomena and process in use in the fields of Education,
                    training, social work, etc. They ensure also a comprehension within the competences of the educational relation and of linguistic dimensions
                    inherent in this situation of specific work. The co");
            WriteLiteral(@"urse lasts three years and builds transverse competences of analysis, comprehension and project
                    realization. In addition it allows the acquisition of knowledge as regards communication and information technologies and of foreign language.
                    More deeply, the purpose of the Bachelor of Sciences in Education is to better accompany the students in their relation with knowledge and of
                    thus better guaranteeing their success.
                </p>

                <h3 class=""smaller_heading""> II.2.2. Specific objectives </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    Commun run with the mention <br/>
                   <strong> The student is able: </strong><br/>
                    With the exit of the course, the undergraduate acquired the basic scientific bases of Education Sciences. He can articulate the knowledge obtained
                    within the framework of the vast fields to clarify the recent or current stakes in Ed");
            WriteLiteral(@"ucation. They are in capacity to synthetize knowledge from
                    various disciplines to clarify an educational issue.<br/>

                    <strong> b. To master specific competences related to the fields of practice: </strong><br/>
                    The student is able to locate himself in the fields in question, in particular to know the institutions, the jobs, the actors and the professional
                    practices. They can locate them from the analytical and diachronic point of view, to include/understand the processes concerned in the
                    contemporary educational phenomena:
                </p>
                <ul class=""one_list"">
                    <li> sociology of education; </li>
